text: Vilma Pegado Nenganga (born 2 November 1996) is an Angolan handball player for Petro de Luanda. Nenganga made its debut in the Angolan national team at the 2015 African games. As a youth player, she was a member of the Angolan team to the 2014 youth olympics. ==Achievements== *Carpathian Trophy: **Winner: 2019 ==References== Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:Angolan female handball players Category:African Games gold medalists for Angola Category:African Games medalists in handball Category:Competitors at the 2015 African Games
